Wash and dry produce.

Halve @lemon{1}. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; roughly chop
into bite-size pieces. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1}; thoroughly pat dry with
#paper towels{}. Roughly tear @prosciutto{2%oz} into bite-size pieces.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @honey Dijon dressing{1.5%oz}, juice from
half the lemon (whole lemon for 4 servings), a pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch}, and as many @chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like.

To bowl with dressing mixture, add lettuce, chickpeas, @Parmesan cheese{6%tbsp},
and @sunflower seeds{0.5%oz}; toss to combine.

Divide salad between bowls. Top with prosciutto and @croutons{1}. Serve.

> This hearty salad is all you need for a light-yet-satisfying lunch. You can
> adjust the chili flakes to your preferred level of heat (or none at all).